The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | I hope belief gets back: Bhowmick
                                                   I hope belief gets back: Bhowmick
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Subhas Bhowmick is hoping that Saturdays victory against Air India will provide his team with much-needed confidence for the remainder of the I-League.         
	I hope this will give the players the confidenceIf the players are confident, the coach will also be happy. Theres no question of relief Theres still a long way left in the league, the East Bengal coach said.         
	Subhas was all praise for Man of the Match Sanju Pradhan. He is the future of Indian football. I will try and protect him much like the way Bhaichung Bhutia was during his early days. I will never play him for 90 minutes If I was coach earlier, I wouldnt have used him for so many matches.         
	Meanwhile, Air India coach Bimal Ghosh said he would lodge a complaint with the All India Football Federation accusing Mohun Bagan of foul play and unethical practice.         
	Michael Tayo was approached by Mohun Bagan officials this morning They wanted to book him for the next season. It disturbed the players concentration and had an effect on his performance.         
	This is unethical and happens only towards the end of the league.... Its only the start of the second phase Knowing well that we had an important match today, they tried to disturb Tayos concentration This is just not done.                                                                                                                       
